var. 
<emphasis box="[282,338,405,431]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="351">elata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Scacchi—and with a more acute spire angle].
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,333,936]" pageId="8" pageNumber="351">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,438,441,468]" pageId="8" pageNumber="351">Material examined:</emphasis>
shells and fragments labelled by Bellini “ 
<taxonomicName authority="V. Salis-Mar Morto" authorityName="V. Salis-Mar Morto" box="[927,1355,441,468]" class="Gastropoda" family="Trochidae" genus="Gibbula" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trochida" pageId="8" pageNumber="351" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="ardens">
<emphasis box="[927,1103,441,467]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="351">Gibbula ardens</emphasis>
V. Salis—Mar Morto
</taxonomicName>
presso il Capo Miseno [Mar Morto near Capo Miseno]” (MCCIC—drawer 145, not numbered) mostly belong to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Payraudeau, 1826)" authorityName="Molluscabase" authorityYear="2019" baseAuthorityName="Payraudeau" baseAuthorityYear="1826" class="Gastropoda" family="Trochidae" genus="Steromphala" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trochida" pageId="8" pageNumber="351" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="adansonii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="351">Steromphala adansonii</emphasis>
(Payraudeau, 1826)
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[620,742,513,539]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1375,1400]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,666,1347]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,666,1347]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 3. A. Gibbula (Magulus) ardens var. acutispira. Original figure. B, C. Gibbula ardens. B. Shells from Mar Morto (Miseno, Bacoli). C. Original label handwritten by Bellini. MCCIC—drawer 145, not numbered. D. Gibbula umbilicaris var. acherusiae. Original figures. E. Trochocochlea castriotae. Original figures. F. Gibbula (Magulus) biasoletti. Shells from Lido di Venezia and original label handwritten by Bellini. MCCIC—drawer 189, not numbered." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3449570" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3449570/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="351">Fig. 3B, C</figureCitation>
). This material comes from the same 
<typeStatus box="[1166,1214,514,540]" pageId="8" pageNumber="351">type</typeStatus>
locality of 
<taxonomicName authority="Bellini, 1903 a" authorityName="Bellini" authorityYear="1903" class="Gastropoda" family="Trochidae" genus="Gibbula" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trochida" pageId="8" pageNumber="351" phylum="Mollusca" rank="variety" species="ardens" subGenus="Magulus" variety="acutispira">
<emphasis box="[1344,1436,513,539]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="351">Gibbula</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[161,259,549,575]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="351">Magulus</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[275,350,549,575]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="351">ardens</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[405,519,550,575]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="351">acutispira</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Bellini, R." box="[526,688,549,575]" pageId="8" pageNumber="351" pagination="20 - 27" refId="ref15673" refString="Bellini, R. (1903 a) I molluschi del Lago Fusaro e del Mar Morto nei Campi Flegrei. Bollettino della Societa dei Naturalisti in Napoli, Series 1, 16, 20 - 27." type="journal article" year="1903">Bellini, 1903a</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
