<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="351" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,333,936]" pageId="8" pageNumber="351">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,317,586,612]" pageId="8" pageNumber="351">Remarks:</emphasis>
having been instituted on the basis of insignificant morphological characteristics, we rank it infrasubspecific, and thus not available (
<bibRefCitation author="ICZN &amp; International Commission on Zoological Nomenclature" box="[560,696,621,647]" pageId="8" pageNumber="351" refId="ref17437" refString="ICZN [International Commission on Zoological Nomenclature] (2012) International code of zoological nomenclature. 4 th Edition. International Trust for Zoological Nomenclature, London. Available from: http: // www. iczn. org / (accessed 15 Feburary 2019)" type="url" year="2012">ICZN 2012</bibRefCitation>
: Art. 
<date box="[760,858,621,648]" pageId="8" pageNumber="351" value="1945-10-02">10.2, 45</date>
.5, 45.6, glossary). This seems to be an overlooked taxon, never reported after its original description apart from 
<bibRefCitation author="Bellini, R." box="[839,1009,657,683]" pageId="8" pageNumber="351" pagination="1 - 87" refId="ref15827" refString="Bellini, R. (1929 a) I molluschi del Golfo di Napoli (studi precedenti, l'ambiente, enumerazione e sinonimia). Annuario del Museo Zoologico della R. Universita di Napoli, 6 (2), 1 - 87." type="journal article" year="1929">Bellini (1929a)</bibRefCitation>
in the general overview of the marine mollusc species living in the Gulf of Naples. Taking into account the figure flanking its description (
<figureCitation box="[1297,1388,693,719]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1375,1400]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,666,1347]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,666,1347]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 3. A. Gibbula (Magulus) ardens var. acutispira. Original figure. B, C. Gibbula ardens. B. Shells from Mar Morto (Miseno, Bacoli). C. Original label handwritten by Bellini. MCCIC—drawer 145, not numbered. D. Gibbula umbilicaris var. acherusiae. Original figures. E. Trochocochlea castriotae. Original figures. F. Gibbula (Magulus) biasoletti. Shells from Lido di Venezia and original label handwritten by Bellini. MCCIC—drawer 189, not numbered." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3449570" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3449570/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="351">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
), its peculiar shape, and the absence of the very similar 
<taxonomicName authority="(Philippi, 1844)" authorityName="Philippi" authorityYear="1844" baseAuthorityName="Philippi" baseAuthorityYear="1844" box="[726,1163,729,755]" class="Gastropoda" family="Trochidae" genus="Steromphala" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trochida" pageId="8" pageNumber="351" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="adriatica">
<emphasis box="[726,978,729,755]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="351">Steromphala adriatica</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Philippi, R. A." box="[993,1154,729,755]" pageId="8" pageNumber="351" refId="ref18455" refString="Philippi, R. A. (1844) Fauna Molluscorum viventium et in tellure tertiaria fossilium regni utriusque Siciliae. Enumeratio Molluscorum Siciliae cum viventium tum in tellure tertiaria fossilium, quae in itinere suo observavit - Volumen secundum. Sumptibus Eduardi Anton, Halis Saxorum, 303 pp." type="book" year="1844">Philippi, 1844</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
in the area, we consider it a misidentification for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Molluscabase" authorityYear="2019" baseAuthorityName="Payraudeau" baseAuthorityYear="1826" box="[427,564,765,792]" class="Gastropoda" family="Trochidae" genus="Steromphala" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trochida" pageId="8" pageNumber="351" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="adansonii">
<emphasis box="[427,564,765,792]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="351">S. adansonii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a nominal taxon that may comprise a complex of cryptic species (
<bibRefCitation author="Barco, A. &amp; Evans, J. &amp; Schembri, P. J. &amp; Taviani, M. &amp; Oliverio, M." pageId="8" pageNumber="351" pagination="785 - 793" refId="ref15479" refString="Barco, A., Evans, J., Schembri, P. J., Taviani, M. &amp; Oliverio, M. (2013) Testing the applicability of DNA barcoding for Mediterranean species of top-shells (Gastropoda, Trochidae, Gibbula s. l.). Marine Biology Research, 9 (8), 785 - 793. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 17451000.2013.765585" type="journal article" year="2013">
Barco 
<emphasis box="[1381,1437,765,791]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="351">et al.</emphasis>
2013
</bibRefCitation>
). This seems to be confirmed by: i) the misidentification reported above; ii) the absence of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Molluscabase" authorityYear="2019" baseAuthorityName="Payraudeau" baseAuthorityYear="1826" box="[1217,1354,801,828]" class="Gastropoda" family="Trochidae" genus="Steromphala" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trochida" pageId="8" pageNumber="351" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="adansonii">
<emphasis box="[1217,1354,801,828]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="351">S. adansonii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
among the species listed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Bellini, R." box="[380,550,837,863]" pageId="8" pageNumber="351" pagination="20 - 27" refId="ref15673" refString="Bellini, R. (1903 a) I molluschi del Lago Fusaro e del Mar Morto nei Campi Flegrei. Bollettino della Societa dei Naturalisti in Napoli, Series 1, 16, 20 - 27." type="journal article" year="1903">Bellini (1903a)</bibRefCitation>
from Mar Morto, despite being among the commonest taxa living in the area of description (authors’ unpublished data); iii) the fact that Bellini was generally unable to correctly identify several of the most common Mediterranean 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rafinesque" authorityYear="1815" box="[529,642,909,935]" class="Gastropoda" family="Trochidae" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="8" pageNumber="351" phylum="Mollusca" rank="family">Trochidae</taxonomicName>
(see also the two subsequent taxa).
</paragraph>
